3
00:00:16,555 --> 00:00:19,395
(Jung Eun Chae)

4
00:00:20,935 --> 00:00:23,735
(Lee Chung Ah)

5
00:00:31,145 --> 00:00:35,115
(Honour)

6
00:00:35,745 --> 00:00:38,585
(Supported by the Culture Ministry
and Korea's Creative Content Agency)

7
00:00:38,945 --> 00:00:39,991
(All people, incidents, and backgrounds...)

8
00:00:40,015 --> 00:00:41,361
(in this drama are fictitious
and unrelated to reality.)

9
00:00:41,385 --> 00:00:43,461
(Also, children and animals were
filmed under production guidelines.)

10
00:00:43,485 --> 00:00:45,225
(Final Episode)

11
00:00:48,455 --> 00:00:51,065
- I'm in.
- Okay, I'm on it.

12
00:00:54,095 --> 00:00:55,471
I put the cameras on a 20-minute loop.

13
00:00:55,495 --> 00:00:56,735
You have to be out before then.

14
00:00:57,665 --> 00:00:59,165
Authentication successful.

15
00:01:07,845 --> 00:01:10,215
Dong Je, you remember what I said, right?

16
00:01:13,185 --> 00:01:15,915
As soon as you're done, go
to Ra Young and Hyun Jin.

17
00:01:19,985 --> 00:01:21,455
Authentication successful.

18
00:01:28,895 --> 00:01:31,605
So, the reason you haven't
caught Han Min Seo

19
00:01:31,965 --> 00:01:33,305
was right here.

20
00:01:39,145 --> 00:01:40,491
(Security alert: Main server access)

21
00:01:40,515 --> 00:01:43,045
(Admin biometric authentication approved)

22
00:01:49,615 --> 00:01:51,055
(Access log, User group: Legal Team)

23
00:01:56,025 --> 00:01:57,895
(Legal Team)

24
00:01:57,965 --> 00:01:59,695
(Kang Shin Jae)

25
00:02:05,205 --> 00:02:08,035
Because of the security network,
it needs external authentication.

26
00:02:08,205 --> 00:02:11,005
That way, if Baek Tae Joo
snoops around, he'll never find it.

27
00:02:11,275 --> 00:02:13,815
It will activate tomorrow
when you enter the code.

28
00:02:13,975 --> 00:02:15,015
All done.

29
00:02:15,075 --> 00:02:17,815
Good. Baek Tae Joo must know by now.

30
00:02:18,085 --> 00:02:19,245
You need to leave right now.

31
00:03:26,745 --> 00:03:29,185
You turn up in the
strangest places, Shin Jae.

32
00:03:31,455 --> 00:03:33,125
Like Bukgwang Hospital yesterday.

33
00:03:33,925 --> 00:03:35,595
And the server room today.

34
00:03:37,995 --> 00:03:39,555
What were you doing in the server room?

35
00:03:40,025 --> 00:03:41,795
If you're so curious, find out for yourself.

36
00:03:44,565 --> 00:03:46,565
Was this your plan all along?

37
00:03:47,305 --> 00:03:49,075
Because your methods are wrong.

38
00:03:50,605 --> 00:03:53,405
But you were on board
with my plan, weren't you?

39
00:03:53,945 --> 00:03:57,845
- That's why you took down Haeil.
- That was my burden to bear.

40
00:03:58,685 --> 00:04:00,685
But this whole thing with
Connect In is different.

41
00:04:02,955 --> 00:04:05,325
Did you say we were essentially
the same kind of people?

42
00:04:05,655 --> 00:04:07,855
Because we are fundamentally
the same kind of people.

43
00:04:08,155 --> 00:04:09,835
People who carry paradise in their hearts,

44
00:04:10,125 --> 00:04:12,425
but are willing to walk into the fiery pit.

45
00:04:14,265 --> 00:04:18,135
Sure, we may be similar, and
have been through similar things.

46
00:04:18,505 --> 00:04:19,905
But the path I chose

47
00:04:20,265 --> 00:04:22,605
was to save the people
trapped in that fiery pit.

48
00:04:24,245 --> 00:04:26,645
No matter what kind of paradise
you think you're protecting,

49
00:04:26,945 --> 00:04:29,875
the moment you dragged
other people into your fiery pit,

50
00:04:30,445 --> 00:04:32,085
you just became another monster.

51
00:04:33,385 --> 00:04:36,485
Just like the countless
people you've destroyed.

52
00:04:42,795 --> 00:04:44,565
I wanted to give you one last chance.

53
00:04:51,765 --> 00:04:53,105
But in the end, you

54
00:04:54,035 --> 00:04:55,805
are no different from the rest.

55
00:04:59,305 --> 00:05:00,305
Fine.

56
00:05:01,415 --> 00:05:02,945
This is our fiery pit.

57
00:05:06,485 --> 00:05:07,515
Do your worst.

58
00:05:21,165 --> 00:05:24,535
Are you crazy? Why are
you only telling us now?

59
00:05:24,605 --> 00:05:27,775
Shin Jae told me not to say
a word until after it was done.

60
00:05:28,435 --> 00:05:31,175
If I'd told you sooner,
she would've killed me.

61
00:05:31,245 --> 00:05:33,405
Did it ever occur to you
that I might kill you myself?

62
00:05:33,545 --> 00:05:37,385
You just left her with Baek Tae
Joo? What if something happens?

63
00:05:40,345 --> 00:05:43,255
No, she's safe for now. With Min Seo gone,

64
00:05:43,315 --> 00:05:45,155
he knows I won't just
sit back and do nothing.

65
00:05:46,125 --> 00:05:48,625
You can track Shin Jae,
right? Where is she now?

66
00:05:48,855 --> 00:05:50,525
I put a tracker on her.

67
00:05:51,195 --> 00:05:53,865
She's in the server room at the IDC.

68
00:05:56,165 --> 00:05:57,165
What'd he say?

69
00:05:58,135 --> 00:06:00,015
It'll be difficult to get
a warrant right away.

70
00:06:00,335 --> 00:06:02,835
- Then what do we do?
- I'll go to the demo venue.

71
00:06:02,905 --> 00:06:04,785
Then Hyun Jin and I
will go to the data center.

72
00:06:05,105 --> 00:06:06,105
I'm counting on you.

73
00:06:10,215 --> 00:06:11,715
The final scan is complete, sir.

74
00:06:12,285 --> 00:06:14,515
The hash check came back clean.

75
00:06:15,185 --> 00:06:17,555
Are you sure? Any backdoors or viruses?

76
00:06:17,785 --> 00:06:19,345
None whatsoever. It's completely clean.

77
00:06:30,235 --> 00:06:32,335
This is an apartment complex in Mujin.

78
00:06:33,835 --> 00:06:35,305
It appears we have an intruder.

79
00:06:36,605 --> 00:06:39,851
With a conventional system,
the victim or a witness

80
00:06:39,875 --> 00:06:43,675
would have to report the crime
before police could be dispatched.

81
00:06:43,985 --> 00:06:47,855
A missing person was reported,
and they were last seen here!

82
00:06:47,915 --> 00:06:50,655
This is a restricted area. You
can't enter without a warrant.

83
00:06:50,725 --> 00:06:52,955
Fine, then at least show
us the CCTV footage!

84
00:06:53,485 --> 00:06:55,201
Come on, you can at
least show us that, right?

85
00:06:55,225 --> 00:06:56,301
All right, I get it. Calm down.

86
00:06:56,325 --> 00:06:58,665
- Come on, you can do that much...
- I told you, no!

87
00:06:58,725 --> 00:07:00,525
- Just a second.
- Sir, please, listen to me!

88
00:07:00,595 --> 00:07:02,565
Unbelievable. A warrant
just to see footage...

89
00:07:02,635 --> 00:07:04,681
But in a city run by The
Prime, things are different.

90
00:07:04,705 --> 00:07:05,935
The Prime's OS

91
00:07:06,335 --> 00:07:08,451
analyses movement and behaviour patterns,

92
00:07:08,475 --> 00:07:10,605
identifying them as a
threat within five seconds.

93
00:07:11,045 --> 00:07:14,175
This information is sent instantly
to the police control center,

94
00:07:14,245 --> 00:07:16,645
and the closest security
team is dispatched.

95
00:07:16,915 --> 00:07:18,395
Before a crime can even be committed,

96
00:07:18,445 --> 00:07:20,245
the threat is eliminated first.

97
00:07:25,055 --> 00:07:27,531
Thank you. After a short break,

98
00:07:27,555 --> 00:07:29,201
we will commence the QnA,

99
00:07:29,225 --> 00:07:30,865
and The Prime's Smart City Demonstration.

100
00:07:31,695 --> 00:07:33,065
Here to congratulate me?

101
00:07:34,335 --> 00:07:35,665
Notice how Shin Jae isn't here?

102
00:07:37,565 --> 00:07:40,005
Aren't you curious where
she might be right now?

103
00:07:45,405 --> 00:07:48,315
Pressing this instantly releases a
clean agent fire suppression gas.

104
00:07:49,015 --> 00:07:51,385
It will remove all the oxygen
from the room Shin Jae is in,

105
00:07:51,845 --> 00:07:53,845
bringing it to zero percent
within three minutes.

106
00:07:55,515 --> 00:07:58,655
I wonder how many minutes
she can last without oxygen.

107
00:07:59,425 --> 00:08:01,055
If you don't want to find out,

108
00:08:03,755 --> 00:08:04,865
keep your mouth shut.

109
00:08:15,405 --> 00:08:16,505
I just got here.

110
00:08:20,405 --> 00:08:22,345
"Is this just a new form of Big Brother?"

111
00:08:22,915 --> 00:08:24,915
I completely understand
the concern you've raised.

112
00:08:25,415 --> 00:08:29,115
But I don't call this
surveillance. I call it protection.

113
00:08:29,485 --> 00:08:34,455
If we can keep our families
safe by giving up a little privacy,

114
00:08:34,595 --> 00:08:38,765
isn't that the best this era
can offer, rather than control?

115
00:08:39,395 --> 00:08:42,295
We have all witnessed too many tragedies.

116
00:08:42,665 --> 00:08:45,735
What the victims of those
tragedies needed most

117
00:08:46,205 --> 00:08:48,905
wasn't privacy. It was survival.

118
00:08:53,245 --> 00:08:54,245
I'm in.

119
00:09:29,375 --> 00:09:30,545
I found Shin Jae.

120
00:09:31,315 --> 00:09:32,315
She's safe.

121
00:09:34,315 --> 00:09:35,515
We found Shin Jae.

122
00:09:36,415 --> 00:09:37,575
Okay, I'm starting on my end.

123
00:09:37,825 --> 00:09:39,585
The system you created.

124
00:09:40,325 --> 00:09:43,055
I wonder how it would
assess your threat level.

125
00:09:45,225 --> 00:09:48,365
Because right now, in
this hall, in this very city,

126
00:09:49,135 --> 00:09:51,105
the most dangerous person

127
00:09:51,865 --> 00:09:52,865
is you, CEO Baek.

128
00:09:57,705 --> 00:10:00,751
Innovation has always
been the greatest threat

129
00:10:00,775 --> 00:10:02,145
to outdated conventions.

130
00:10:04,545 --> 00:10:07,615
So, shall we find out how
threatening our system can be?

131
00:10:22,165 --> 00:10:24,235
(Releasing suppression gas)

132
00:10:49,495 --> 00:10:50,495
Darn.

133
00:10:52,565 --> 00:10:53,565
I'm talking about

134
00:10:54,365 --> 00:10:56,195
a man who trampled on human dignity

135
00:10:56,595 --> 00:11:00,035
behind the vague ideas
of innovation and justice.

136
00:11:01,135 --> 00:11:04,375
A man who, for his own gain,
created the Connect In app.

137
00:11:05,705 --> 00:11:09,415
A man who used that app to
make countless victims suffer.

138
00:11:10,775 --> 00:11:12,295
The man standing right in front of me.

139
00:11:12,545 --> 00:11:13,715
CEO Baek Tae Joo.

140
00:11:19,055 --> 00:11:22,125
What was the authentication code
Shin Jae set up during the demo?

141
00:11:22,295 --> 00:11:25,595
For our 20th anniversary, shall we
go to Jeju Island? The three of us?

142
00:11:25,795 --> 00:11:28,235
Just Jeju? We should go
to the Maldives, at least.

143
00:11:33,005 --> 00:11:36,305
You set a trap using prostitution as bait?

144
00:11:37,505 --> 00:11:38,775
Think of the outcome, Shin Jae.

145
00:11:39,175 --> 00:11:42,075
If this can completely
clean up this rotten system,

146
00:11:42,145 --> 00:11:44,591
- Gosh, this is driving me nuts!
- Isn't that an outcome you'd want?

147
00:11:44,615 --> 00:11:45,895
Why on earth isn't this working?

148
00:11:46,615 --> 00:11:47,915
That's nonsense.

149
00:11:48,515 --> 00:11:50,155
Do you even hear yourself right now?

150
00:11:50,655 --> 00:11:52,985
That means you used the victims as bait.

151
00:11:53,325 --> 00:11:54,855
What about the victims' pain?

152
00:11:55,255 --> 00:11:57,001
- I said, turn it off!
- You don't care what happens?

153
00:11:57,025 --> 00:11:58,895
The system is frozen. I've lost control.

154
00:11:58,965 --> 00:12:00,895
You know how it is, Shin Jae.

155
00:12:01,765 --> 00:12:05,535
How do you cut out a festering
wound without shedding blood?

156
00:12:09,575 --> 00:12:11,605
(Emergency)

157
00:12:13,305 --> 00:12:14,315
What's that?

158
00:12:16,045 --> 00:12:17,045
It's a person!

159
00:12:31,325 --> 00:12:32,605
The video you're watching now

160
00:12:33,095 --> 00:12:37,365
shows CEO Baek Tae Joo
attempting to murder a witness

161
00:12:37,735 --> 00:12:39,005
to cover up his own crimes.

162
00:12:40,365 --> 00:12:41,975
What is that? Is that a person?

163
00:12:43,775 --> 00:12:44,775
Is this for real?

164
00:12:46,275 --> 00:12:47,275
What is going on?

165
00:12:53,285 --> 00:12:54,285
That's a person!

166
00:12:57,415 --> 00:12:58,785
Seon Kyu, can you hear me?

167
00:13:00,225 --> 00:13:01,225
Seon Kyu!

168
00:13:01,955 --> 00:13:02,955
Honey!

169
00:13:03,495 --> 00:13:04,495
Hyun Jin.

170
00:13:06,465 --> 00:13:07,465
Hyun Jin!

171
00:13:09,695 --> 00:13:10,695
(Emergency elevator)

172
00:13:43,595 --> 00:13:46,605
We are one step away
from a whole new world.

173
00:13:47,435 --> 00:13:49,111
Why must humans ruin everything

174
00:13:49,135 --> 00:13:51,945
because they can't bear to
shed the last drop of blood?

175
00:13:53,005 --> 00:13:54,475
But the path I chose

176
00:13:54,575 --> 00:13:56,945
was to save the people
trapped in that fiery pit.

177
00:13:57,245 --> 00:13:59,521
No matter what kind of paradise
you think you're protecting,

178
00:13:59,545 --> 00:14:02,485
the moment you dragged
other people into your fiery pit,

179
00:14:02,955 --> 00:14:04,425
you just became another monster.

180
00:14:23,505 --> 00:14:28,315
(Sehan Hospital)

181
00:14:43,455 --> 00:14:44,465
So, what happened?

182
00:14:45,895 --> 00:14:46,895
The Maldives.

183
00:14:49,895 --> 00:14:51,235
So it all worked out, then.

184
00:14:51,865 --> 00:14:54,375
How could you think
of betting your own life?

185
00:14:54,705 --> 00:14:56,175
What if something had gone wrong?

186
00:14:57,205 --> 00:14:59,205
That's why I sent Dong Je to you.

187
00:15:00,245 --> 00:15:03,445
Was this your plan from the start?
Why didn't you tell me sooner?

188
00:15:05,015 --> 00:15:06,685
Too many things were tangled up in it.

189
00:15:07,085 --> 00:15:09,655
To unravel it all, this was the only way.

190
00:15:11,585 --> 00:15:12,585
Are you okay?

191
00:15:15,925 --> 00:15:17,395
You've been through so much.

192
00:15:18,165 --> 00:15:19,205
I'm asking if you're okay.

193
00:15:21,865 --> 00:15:23,105
If you're asking about Haeil...

194
00:15:23,835 --> 00:15:25,765
Even if I'm not okay, I have to live with it.

195
00:15:26,235 --> 00:15:28,035
That's why I did all this in the first place.

196
00:15:32,645 --> 00:15:34,305
Go to my place, Ra Young.

197
00:15:35,345 --> 00:15:36,615
Min Seo is waiting for you.

198
00:15:40,585 --> 00:15:41,585
Okay.

199
00:15:42,585 --> 00:15:43,685
But before I do,

200
00:15:44,755 --> 00:15:46,225
I want to check on Hyun Jin.

201
00:16:05,805 --> 00:16:08,215
(Put the used gowns here.)

202
00:16:12,515 --> 00:16:14,285
(Authorized personnel only)

203
00:16:15,585 --> 00:16:16,585
Hyun Jin!

204
00:16:22,425 --> 00:16:24,355
(Intensive Care Unit)

205
00:18:26,585 --> 00:18:28,355
You came that day, didn't you?

206
00:18:29,415 --> 00:18:30,415
To the hospital.

207
00:18:35,495 --> 00:18:37,395
I was going to call
and tell you I was okay,

208
00:18:38,295 --> 00:18:40,025
but Attorney Kang told me to wait.

209
00:18:42,365 --> 00:18:43,365
I heard.

210
00:18:50,335 --> 00:18:52,245
I'm going to turn myself in.

211
00:18:53,475 --> 00:18:56,415
And I'm going to tell them
everything Baek Tae Joo did.

212
00:19:01,985 --> 00:19:02,985
Okay.

213
00:19:04,285 --> 00:19:05,855
I'll go with you tomorrow.

214
00:19:13,765 --> 00:19:14,765
But before that,

215
00:19:16,165 --> 00:19:17,165
let's go home.

216
00:19:58,175 --> 00:19:59,475
Here, I'm giving this back.

217
00:20:17,255 --> 00:20:18,325
Can I

218
00:20:19,465 --> 00:20:20,725
sleep with you tonight?

219
00:21:15,415 --> 00:21:17,985
This will be the last night I sleep like this.

220
00:21:20,225 --> 00:21:21,745
Starting tomorrow, I'm going to try

221
00:21:22,195 --> 00:21:23,895
sleeping in the bedroom again.

222
00:21:31,295 --> 00:21:32,305
Are you scared?

223
00:21:34,105 --> 00:21:35,635
About turning yourself in tomorrow.

224
00:21:36,975 --> 00:21:37,975
A little.

225
00:21:42,915 --> 00:21:45,085
You know how in the movies,

226
00:21:45,445 --> 00:21:48,415
no matter what their child
has done, they'll do anything

227
00:21:49,115 --> 00:21:51,015
to hide them.

228
00:21:51,985 --> 00:21:55,295
Do you wish I would do that for you?

229
00:21:56,155 --> 00:21:57,155
No.

230
00:21:58,495 --> 00:22:00,495
Just come with me.

231
00:22:02,395 --> 00:22:03,535
That's all I need.

232
00:22:05,635 --> 00:22:06,635
Okay.

233
00:22:07,935 --> 00:22:09,005
I will.

234
00:22:21,185 --> 00:22:22,385
Hey.

235
00:22:26,825 --> 00:22:27,855
I still

236
00:22:28,755 --> 00:22:31,325
haven't been able to forgive anything.

237
00:22:33,925 --> 00:22:38,565
I don't understand why I
had to go through all of this.

238
00:22:42,305 --> 00:22:45,175
But if this is the end,

239
00:22:45,775 --> 00:22:47,445
it would feel so terribly unfair.

240
00:22:50,145 --> 00:22:51,275
After all the hating,

241
00:22:52,415 --> 00:22:53,485
and the loathing,

242
00:22:54,985 --> 00:22:56,285
and the pain.

243
00:22:58,425 --> 00:23:00,185
I want to see

244
00:23:01,995 --> 00:23:03,295
what's on the other side.

245
00:23:10,335 --> 00:23:11,535
So until then,

246
00:23:13,135 --> 00:23:15,605
can you wait for me here?

247
00:23:21,145 --> 00:23:22,145
Yes.

248
00:23:23,545 --> 00:23:25,185
I'll be right here, waiting.

249
00:23:28,855 --> 00:23:32,285
It might take my whole life.

250
00:23:34,155 --> 00:23:37,595
I'm just so broken.

251
00:24:03,655 --> 00:24:05,155
You're not broken.

252
00:24:06,755 --> 00:24:08,395
We've just had to go through

253
00:24:09,325 --> 00:24:10,625
a deeper,

254
00:24:11,395 --> 00:24:13,795
and darker tunnel than
most people. That's all.

255
00:24:15,895 --> 00:24:19,435
The important thing is
that, despite everything,

256
00:24:20,835 --> 00:24:22,175
we're here,

257
00:24:24,475 --> 00:24:25,475
and we

258
00:24:27,045 --> 00:24:28,645
survived.

259
00:24:58,705 --> 00:25:00,545
What are you doing here?

260
00:25:08,485 --> 00:25:10,515
(Sehan Hospital)

261
00:25:32,245 --> 00:25:33,245
You idiot.

262
00:25:35,175 --> 00:25:36,845
How long are you going to keep sleeping?

263
00:25:38,345 --> 00:25:39,515
Wake up. That's enough.

264
00:25:43,285 --> 00:25:45,025
I refuse to be a widow.

265
00:25:46,285 --> 00:25:48,125
You are not allowed to die like this.

266
00:25:49,425 --> 00:25:51,795
I won't let you. Got it?

267
00:26:09,015 --> 00:26:11,375
Did they say it was okay
for you to leave this early?

268
00:26:12,515 --> 00:26:15,455
I'm fine. Nothing's seriously
wrong thanks to Seon Kyu.

269
00:26:17,055 --> 00:26:18,585
How's Seon Kyu?

270
00:26:19,055 --> 00:26:20,555
Same as yesterday.

271
00:26:20,925 --> 00:26:22,725
They want to observe
him for a few more days.

272
00:26:24,625 --> 00:26:27,265
We'll come every day for a
while. Let's wait together

273
00:26:28,265 --> 00:26:29,835
until Seon Kyu wakes up.

274
00:26:32,965 --> 00:26:35,035
Have you talked to Min Seo?

275
00:26:35,905 --> 00:26:36,905
A little.

276
00:26:38,205 --> 00:26:40,245
It looked like she was
planning to turn herself in.

277
00:26:40,445 --> 00:26:42,645
Yes. I'm going with her today.

278
00:26:43,015 --> 00:26:44,675
Her sentence won't be light.

279
00:26:45,585 --> 00:26:48,655
She knows. I think
she's prepared to face it.

280
00:26:52,125 --> 00:26:55,155
Shin Jae, what are your plans now?

281
00:26:56,725 --> 00:26:58,725
We got an office space.

282
00:26:59,025 --> 00:27:00,695
We're moving in next month.

283
00:27:01,495 --> 00:27:02,635
Come back to us.

284
00:27:02,965 --> 00:27:06,005
And we need to get serious
about the Connect In lawsuit.

285
00:27:06,065 --> 00:27:07,065
I'm

286
00:27:09,235 --> 00:27:10,835
not going back to LnJ.

287
00:27:12,775 --> 00:27:13,775
At least, not for now.

288
00:27:18,715 --> 00:27:23,255
(Courthouse)

289
00:27:31,495 --> 00:27:34,195
Can I have a word with her for a moment?

290
00:27:50,215 --> 00:27:51,545
Did you come here

291
00:27:52,515 --> 00:27:54,115
just to watch me get locked up?

292
00:27:55,815 --> 00:27:59,325
I came to give you what
you wanted so badly.

293
00:28:02,095 --> 00:28:03,495
Your position...

294
00:28:03,795 --> 00:28:05,125
Give it to me.

295
00:28:05,765 --> 00:28:09,065
From now on, I'll take charge of Haeil.

296
00:28:14,305 --> 00:28:16,675
Do you think I was trying to leave you

297
00:28:18,035 --> 00:28:20,205
nothing but a pile of ruins?

298
00:28:23,045 --> 00:28:25,685
Someone has to take responsibility
for this mess and clean it up.

299
00:28:26,345 --> 00:28:27,845
And as your daughter,

300
00:28:28,415 --> 00:28:30,015
that's my responsibility now.

301
00:28:34,485 --> 00:28:35,895
It took all of this for me

302
00:28:38,525 --> 00:28:40,565
to finally live as your daughter, Mom.

303
00:28:48,975 --> 00:28:50,275
Ever since you were little,

304
00:28:52,045 --> 00:28:54,605
you've always been so much like me.

305
00:28:58,945 --> 00:29:00,445
I still am, Mom.

306
00:29:12,765 --> 00:29:16,235
Ma'am, the review results are in.
The arrest warrant has been issued.

307
00:29:16,395 --> 00:29:18,715
You'll have to be transferred
to the detention center now.

308
00:29:38,725 --> 00:29:39,965
What do you think you're doing?

309
00:29:40,955 --> 00:29:43,355
If you're going to endure this,
then do it without wavering.

310
00:29:43,495 --> 00:29:45,325
The work you're about to take on

311
00:29:46,195 --> 00:29:47,265
is exactly like this.

312
00:30:23,695 --> 00:30:25,905
What is your relationship to the suspect?

313
00:30:26,665 --> 00:30:28,041
I'm her lawyer.

314
00:30:28,065 --> 00:30:30,575
And her family.

315
00:30:33,205 --> 00:30:36,445
(Sehan Hospital)

316
00:31:12,915 --> 00:31:13,915
Hyun Jin.

317
00:31:21,155 --> 00:31:25,565
(Intensive Care Unit)

318
00:31:42,745 --> 00:31:44,591
Attorney Yoon, what are your thoughts

319
00:31:44,615 --> 00:31:46,491
on today's verdict for the
Connect-In defendants?

320
00:31:46,515 --> 00:31:47,961
I believe this is the
worst possible outcome.

321
00:31:47,985 --> 00:31:50,985
- Can you tell us why you think so?
- What are your reasons?

322
00:31:51,555 --> 00:31:54,385
Ten years for soliciting murder,
five for bribery and abuse of power.

323
00:31:54,425 --> 00:31:57,055
But what about the sexual assault charges?

324
00:31:57,455 --> 00:32:01,125
In the end, every defendant got off
with a fine on prostitution charges.

325
00:32:01,565 --> 00:32:04,565
Punishment was only handed
down for corruption by those in power,

326
00:32:04,635 --> 00:32:07,835
while totally ignoring the
suffering of the victims.

327
00:32:08,065 --> 00:32:10,875
We will absolutely not accept

328
00:32:11,505 --> 00:32:12,775
this half-measure of a verdict.

329
00:32:14,845 --> 00:32:18,545
(Courthouse)

330
00:32:25,785 --> 00:32:29,125
Seriously? Have these
jerks lost their minds?

331
00:32:29,395 --> 00:32:32,725
And Judge Kim, has he lost his mind?
I mean, this was a sex assault case,

332
00:32:32,795 --> 00:32:35,225
and he says to add
prostitution to the indictment?

333
00:32:35,295 --> 00:32:37,055
Don't even get me
started on the prosecutor.

334
00:32:37,165 --> 00:32:39,065
He just went along with it like a coward.

335
00:32:41,335 --> 00:32:42,535
They'll appeal, right?

336
00:32:43,205 --> 00:32:44,675
We have to force their hand.

337
00:32:44,975 --> 00:32:48,605
- This is just the beginning.
- You think we'll let this go?

338
00:32:49,215 --> 00:32:52,715
The civil suit hasn't
even really started yet.

339
00:32:55,185 --> 00:32:58,555
(Mujin Forensic Science Institute)

340
00:33:01,055 --> 00:33:02,525
(Forensic Analysis Department)

341
00:33:02,595 --> 00:33:03,655
What do you think?

342
00:33:04,825 --> 00:33:08,095
It's hard to tell if it's CEO
Baek Tae Joo just by looking.

343
00:33:08,695 --> 00:33:10,335
The body is in such...

344
00:33:10,635 --> 00:33:11,765
It's severely decomposed.

345
00:33:12,465 --> 00:33:14,105
Still, I asked you to come, just in case.

346
00:33:14,505 --> 00:33:17,335
I was hoping for a visual
ID before the results come in.

347
00:33:18,335 --> 00:33:19,345
And this.

348
00:33:19,945 --> 00:33:22,245
These are the personal
effects found with the body.

349
00:33:24,445 --> 00:33:28,515
This looks similar to
the one CEO Baek used.

350
00:33:29,755 --> 00:33:32,425
The clothes, the physical build...

351
00:33:33,125 --> 00:33:35,725
It's looking more and more
likely that it's CEO Baek.

352
00:33:36,155 --> 00:33:40,125
So the police are assuming
that CEO Baek is likely dead?

353
00:33:40,225 --> 00:33:42,041
There have been no signs
of life since he vanished

354
00:33:42,065 --> 00:33:43,895
on the night of the demonstration.

355
00:33:44,235 --> 00:33:46,935
No record he left the country,
and no reported sightings.

356
00:33:47,505 --> 00:33:50,105
Given the circumstances,
we suspect this was retaliation.

357
00:33:51,335 --> 00:33:53,705
It wouldn't be surprising
if the users were behind it.

358
00:33:53,775 --> 00:33:55,305
(Morgue, Autopsy Room)

359
00:33:55,375 --> 00:33:58,375
So is that body really CEO Baek?

360
00:33:59,415 --> 00:34:02,085
I'll let you know as soon as
the DNA match results are in.

361
00:34:02,285 --> 00:34:04,055
Thanks for your help today.

362
00:34:06,455 --> 00:34:08,525
It's great seeing you reinstated.

363
00:34:10,195 --> 00:34:12,395
I heard you went to bat for me.

364
00:34:14,165 --> 00:34:15,265
I only restored

365
00:34:15,795 --> 00:34:17,565
what was wrong to its original state.

366
00:34:19,105 --> 00:34:21,535
Still, thank you. Let's go.

367
00:34:51,295 --> 00:34:53,905
Attorney Yoon, you really dressed up today.

368
00:34:55,335 --> 00:34:58,135
But there was video evidence
of the assault, wasn't there?

369
00:34:58,205 --> 00:35:02,975
There was also drug use and duress,
so how was this verdict possible?

370
00:35:03,815 --> 00:35:06,091
They ruled the blatant felony
was the sole crime of Park Je Yeol,

371
00:35:06,115 --> 00:35:08,591
the deceased prosecutor.

372
00:35:08,615 --> 00:35:11,085
And they let the other
perpetrators get away with it.

373
00:35:11,655 --> 00:35:15,595
This ruling is dangerous because
the court has given perpetrators

374
00:35:15,655 --> 00:35:17,525
a playbook on how to get away with it.

375
00:35:18,255 --> 00:35:22,435
You can assault and abuse
anyone as long as you pay them off.

376
00:35:22,495 --> 00:35:25,435
This doesn't just victimize
them all over again,

377
00:35:25,665 --> 00:35:29,705
but it will also set a precedent
creating many more "Connect Ins."

378
00:35:30,735 --> 00:35:31,851
(Late Prosecutor Park
Je Yeol, a sole perpetrator)

379
00:35:31,875 --> 00:35:32,921
("A Questionable Verdict, Public Outcry")

380
00:35:32,945 --> 00:35:34,051
("Movement for
'Anti-Connect In Act' Grows")

381
00:35:34,075 --> 00:35:37,215
The special bill under review
in the National Assembly

382
00:35:37,275 --> 00:35:40,515
is focused on closing two major loopholes.

383
00:35:40,745 --> 00:35:43,355
First, it expands the
definition of an accomplice.

384
00:35:43,455 --> 00:35:45,391
If someone purchased sex
within an exploitative system,

385
00:35:45,415 --> 00:35:47,985
they'd be considered an
accomplice to sexual assault.

386
00:35:48,185 --> 00:35:51,425
Second, it enhances penalties
for special circumstances.

387
00:35:51,695 --> 00:35:54,925
In cases like this one, with
organised threats and coercion,

388
00:35:55,065 --> 00:35:59,035
any monetary transaction
would not be legitimate consent.

389
00:35:59,135 --> 00:36:01,565
That's the core of this new bill.

390
00:36:04,605 --> 00:36:08,705
That's a powerful swing for
someone with spinal stenosis.

391
00:36:09,215 --> 00:36:11,575
- Who are these people?
- Go ahead.

392
00:36:13,245 --> 00:36:16,155
Hey, that's a limited edition!
Keep your hands off it!

393
00:36:16,255 --> 00:36:18,485
Hey! Do you have any
idea who you're dealing with?

394
00:36:18,715 --> 00:36:21,525
I know exactly who you are. A sex offender.

395
00:36:22,025 --> 00:36:23,871
You're aware of the civil
suit against you, right?

396
00:36:23,895 --> 00:36:26,301
We're here to seize your movable assets

397
00:36:26,325 --> 00:36:28,471
before the verdict comes in,
in case you try to hide them.

398
00:36:28,495 --> 00:36:31,195
And we've already paid
a visit to your house.

399
00:36:35,675 --> 00:36:36,711
("Former Minister Yeo Min Seok...")

400
00:36:36,735 --> 00:36:38,151
("Feigning Illness in the Hospital Bed")

401
00:36:38,175 --> 00:36:39,681
("LnJ Declares War Against
the Users of Connect In")

402
00:36:39,705 --> 00:36:42,105
(If it's a war, see it through.
(There's no backing out now.)

403
00:36:44,875 --> 00:36:47,985
("LnJ Declares War Against
the Users of Connect In")

404
00:36:53,555 --> 00:36:54,585
When did you get here?

405
00:36:54,925 --> 00:36:55,925
A little while ago.

406
00:36:56,525 --> 00:36:59,325
You should've called. We
could've grabbed a bite.

407
00:36:59,895 --> 00:37:02,835
It's no big deal. We
can eat some other time.

408
00:37:03,265 --> 00:37:05,965
She's right. She'll probably
be back tomorrow anyway.

409
00:37:06,065 --> 00:37:08,265
Hey, for your information, I
don't come here every day.

410
00:37:09,005 --> 00:37:10,935
They're right. You probably come here

411
00:37:11,005 --> 00:37:13,745
more often than I do. And I work here now.

412
00:37:13,845 --> 00:37:17,245
Kang Shin Jae, you should start
chipping in for rent, you know?

413
00:37:17,315 --> 00:37:20,785
We're taking every case we can
get just to keep this place afloat,

414
00:37:20,845 --> 00:37:23,615
we're working ourselves to death.
And living with this empty desk

415
00:37:23,685 --> 00:37:25,725
is making this place feel
cramped, it's killing me.

416
00:37:26,425 --> 00:37:29,895
Hey. I brought this for you instead.

417
00:37:30,255 --> 00:37:31,355
This is the good stuff.

418
00:37:34,265 --> 00:37:36,265
- This feels like a bribe.
- Here you go.

419
00:37:36,835 --> 00:37:38,895
It's a bribe.

420
00:37:39,165 --> 00:37:40,165
Thanks.

421
00:37:49,675 --> 00:37:53,445
What is this? A health potion? I
feel so recharged after one sip.

422
00:37:54,685 --> 00:37:56,605
I heard you got your
business cards. Let me see!

423
00:37:59,185 --> 00:38:00,225
Here you go.

424
00:38:01,525 --> 00:38:03,595
You're a team manager?
What about your team?

425
00:38:03,925 --> 00:38:06,125
- It's a team of one.
- Goodness.

426
00:38:10,035 --> 00:38:11,335
Attorney Kang, you're here.

427
00:38:12,235 --> 00:38:13,411
Are you back from the courthouse?

428
00:38:13,435 --> 00:38:16,435
Yes. I was showing Su Eun
how to copy the case files.

429
00:38:16,675 --> 00:38:18,935
- Hello.
- How have you been?

430
00:38:19,275 --> 00:38:21,005
How are the others doing?

431
00:38:21,075 --> 00:38:24,875
Yes. Da Eun's back in school,
and Min Jae just became a manager,

432
00:38:24,945 --> 00:38:26,945
so he bought us a meal to celebrate.

433
00:38:27,385 --> 00:38:28,885
I miss seeing them all.

434
00:38:29,615 --> 00:38:33,885
- And how's the internship going?
- Good. I'm still learning,

435
00:38:34,455 --> 00:38:35,535
but I'm really enjoying it.

436
00:38:36,355 --> 00:38:37,525
It's rewarding too.

437
00:38:37,925 --> 00:38:41,565
Once something's in her brain,
she instantly recalls case numbers.

438
00:38:41,795 --> 00:38:45,665
- She'll be after my job soon.
- That's what I like to hear.

439
00:38:46,665 --> 00:38:49,135
In that case, Ye Ji, you can
come back to Haeil with me.

440
00:38:49,205 --> 00:38:51,375
I've been struggling to
hold down the fort by myself.

441
00:38:51,435 --> 00:38:52,981
- And it's so exhausting.
- Listen to you.

442
00:38:53,005 --> 00:38:55,145
Trying to steal our star player, are you?

443
00:38:55,505 --> 00:38:59,715
Instead of me going back, why
not come back to us, Attorney?

444
00:39:02,615 --> 00:39:04,185
I should get going.

445
00:39:05,955 --> 00:39:07,255
Don't you give my spot away.

446
00:39:07,555 --> 00:39:11,625
- Then you'd better hurry back.
- After I'm done cleaning.

447
00:39:16,465 --> 00:39:18,865
Attorney Kang looked so drained.

448
00:39:20,565 --> 00:39:22,635
She's facing a ton of lawsuits.

449
00:39:22,705 --> 00:39:24,511
And the amount she'll have
to pay for fines and damages

450
00:39:24,535 --> 00:39:25,535
is astronomical.

451
00:39:25,605 --> 00:39:27,351
She must be under a
lot of stress these days.

452
00:39:27,375 --> 00:39:30,615
Part of me just wants her to quit,

453
00:39:30,675 --> 00:39:32,585
and come back here without a care.

454
00:39:33,545 --> 00:39:37,685
But that's not who Kang Shin
Jae is. She'd never do that.

455
00:39:56,005 --> 00:39:57,605
Look at you, doing so well for yourself.

456
00:39:59,645 --> 00:40:01,075
What strings did you pull?

457
00:40:03,145 --> 00:40:04,985
Pinning the murder-for-hire
on Park Je Yeol,

458
00:40:05,245 --> 00:40:07,445
and framing my mother
for Haeil's corruption...

459
00:40:07,885 --> 00:40:10,331
That shouldn't be enough for
you to be walking around scot-free.

460
00:40:10,355 --> 00:40:12,231
Let's just say I cashed
in an insurance policy.

461
00:40:12,255 --> 00:40:14,655
I've had a few things
tucked away for a rainy day.

462
00:40:16,725 --> 00:40:19,125
You talk as if the verdict
is already set in stone.

463
00:40:19,495 --> 00:40:20,625
Time will tell.

464
00:40:21,825 --> 00:40:22,935
Here. Take a look at this.

465
00:40:31,335 --> 00:40:32,645
(Complaint)

466
00:40:32,705 --> 00:40:34,505
(Claim for damages)

467
00:40:35,475 --> 00:40:39,415
- What is this?
- Connect In members hurt by this

468
00:40:39,585 --> 00:40:41,915
have filed a class-action
lawsuit against Haeil.

469
00:40:42,545 --> 00:40:45,015
Astronomical penalties on top of damages.

470
00:40:45,515 --> 00:40:49,185
Haeil won't be able to
afford that in its current state.

471
00:40:50,355 --> 00:40:52,195
You're telling me you're
behind this lawsuit?

472
00:40:52,395 --> 00:40:53,725
I'm merely an advisor.

473
00:40:54,225 --> 00:40:57,195
The company looked
like a wreck on my way in.

474
00:40:58,035 --> 00:40:59,875
You're finally starting to get it, aren't you?

475
00:41:00,135 --> 00:41:02,065
The real consequences of your choices.

476
00:41:04,935 --> 00:41:07,075
You poached all of our key attorneys,

477
00:41:07,475 --> 00:41:09,555
and now you plan to cripple
the firm with a lawsuit?

478
00:41:10,775 --> 00:41:12,745
What do you really want?

479
00:41:13,515 --> 00:41:14,515
This room.

480
00:41:16,385 --> 00:41:17,455
That seat.

481
00:41:17,915 --> 00:41:19,285
That's what I want.

482
00:41:21,885 --> 00:41:23,955
Is Haeil still the same
company it used to be?

483
00:41:24,455 --> 00:41:26,395
Why are you so obsessed with Haeil?

484
00:41:26,865 --> 00:41:28,225
Because it was my life's work.

485
00:41:29,195 --> 00:41:32,965
I poured my blood, sweat,
and tears into building it.

486
00:41:34,035 --> 00:41:37,275
To see Haeil crumble so pointlessly
due to your childish recklessness,

487
00:41:37,875 --> 00:41:39,175
I will not tolerate it.

488
00:41:41,375 --> 00:41:43,115
I'm going to rebuild it from scratch.

489
00:41:43,645 --> 00:41:44,815
The right way, this time.

490
00:41:45,175 --> 00:41:46,845
By cutting out all the rot at its core.

491
00:41:47,485 --> 00:41:50,155
Fine. And in return,

492
00:41:50,885 --> 00:41:52,565
you'll be buried under a mountain of debt.

493
00:41:56,825 --> 00:41:58,155
Remember this, Shin Jae.

494
00:41:58,895 --> 00:42:01,725
Justice is expensive. Like a super car.

495
00:42:02,325 --> 00:42:04,395
At first glance, it's flashy and looks cool,

496
00:42:04,435 --> 00:42:06,865
and you might feel great behind the wheel,

497
00:42:07,335 --> 00:42:10,435
but it costs you an absurd amount
to get to the same destination.

498
00:42:13,145 --> 00:42:14,465
Good. I like that it's expensive.

499
00:42:15,275 --> 00:42:17,515
If it were something cheap and easy to get,

500
00:42:17,945 --> 00:42:19,815
what would be the point of fighting for it?

501
00:42:24,455 --> 00:42:25,485
Soon enough,

502
00:42:25,785 --> 00:42:27,485
you'll be ready to throw in the towel.

503
00:42:27,855 --> 00:42:28,925
We'll talk again then.

504
00:42:56,285 --> 00:42:57,285
(VVIP invitation)

505
00:43:00,255 --> 00:43:01,525
(VVIP invitation)

506
00:43:01,585 --> 00:43:02,585
(Incoming call)

507
00:43:07,065 --> 00:43:08,395
Yes, Kwon Jung Hyeon speaking.

508
00:43:13,265 --> 00:43:15,435
You look even better in person, Yoo Na.

509
00:43:16,035 --> 00:43:17,175
And your look is fantastic.

510
00:43:18,075 --> 00:43:21,545
I can see why our client picked you.

511
00:43:22,375 --> 00:43:23,375
Thank you.

512
00:43:24,715 --> 00:43:27,445
So, what's the brand name exactly?

513
00:43:27,945 --> 00:43:30,485
I tried looking it up, but nothing came up.

514
00:43:31,585 --> 00:43:32,585
Of course you couldn't.

515
00:43:33,085 --> 00:43:35,255
It's not a brand for the general public.

516
00:43:36,525 --> 00:43:40,395
It's a high-end brand invested
by the Middle East royalty.

517
00:43:40,825 --> 00:43:43,265
Only a handful of VVIPs know about it.

518
00:43:45,395 --> 00:43:47,265
The guests at this party

519
00:43:47,805 --> 00:43:49,475
are beyond anything you can imagine.

520
00:43:49,775 --> 00:43:54,005
These are people you'd never share
the same room with in your lifetime.

521
00:43:54,675 --> 00:43:56,615
If you post just one picture with them,

522
00:43:56,875 --> 00:43:59,515
it'll completely elevate
your social media status.

523
00:44:08,225 --> 00:44:09,355
Here's the invitation.

524
00:44:12,195 --> 00:44:13,495
The time and location

525
00:44:13,865 --> 00:44:16,295
will be revealed on the
event day for security reasons.

526
00:44:17,595 --> 00:44:19,165
(First class board)

527
00:44:20,735 --> 00:44:22,265
It's a first-class ticket.

528
00:44:23,005 --> 00:44:25,205
Like I said, it's on a whole other level.

529
00:44:26,545 --> 00:44:29,845
All you have to do is show
up and have a good time.

530
00:44:31,375 --> 00:44:35,015
(VVIP invitation)

531
00:44:35,085 --> 00:44:37,885
(Haeil Law Firm)

532
00:44:41,025 --> 00:44:42,895
(CEO Kang Shin Jae)

533
00:44:56,475 --> 00:44:59,945
(The late Seo Ji Yoon)

534
00:45:30,805 --> 00:45:33,245
(The late Seo Ji Yoon)

535
00:45:43,815 --> 00:45:44,885
Take a look.

536
00:45:45,485 --> 00:45:47,055
All you have to do is sign.

537
00:46:01,435 --> 00:46:05,035
I've been thinking. And I
can't agree to the divorce.

538
00:46:05,905 --> 00:46:08,845
If you really want one, sue me.
That is, if you think you can win.

539
00:46:10,045 --> 00:46:12,415
- Hyun Jin.
- That doesn't matter to me anymore.

540
00:46:13,345 --> 00:46:16,415
Call me shameless or point fingers at me,

541
00:46:16,985 --> 00:46:18,815
none of it matters to me anymore.

542
00:46:19,785 --> 00:46:23,595
I don't care if I have to
be awful, selfish, and cruel.

543
00:46:24,195 --> 00:46:25,855
Just please, don't leave me.

544
00:46:30,535 --> 00:46:33,165
If this is about what I said before

545
00:46:33,405 --> 00:46:34,765
I was being flippant.

546
00:46:36,575 --> 00:46:39,275
I had no idea what
it'd feel like to lose you.

547
00:46:39,945 --> 00:46:41,945
Acting like I wouldn't care if we broke up.

548
00:46:42,245 --> 00:46:43,615
Like I'd be fine.

549
00:46:47,715 --> 00:46:49,185
Back at the hospital,

550
00:46:49,715 --> 00:46:51,635
I was the most scared
I've ever been in my life.

551
00:46:54,885 --> 00:46:56,595
That was the scariest moment for me too.

552
00:46:58,425 --> 00:47:00,025
I was losing consciousness,

553
00:47:00,825 --> 00:47:03,135
and I thought I'd never
get to see you again.

554
00:47:04,165 --> 00:47:06,445
I realised that if we see each
other and smile every day,

555
00:47:07,265 --> 00:47:09,365
nothing else in the world matters.

556
00:47:10,775 --> 00:47:11,905
That's how I felt.

557
00:47:17,675 --> 00:47:18,775
Then

558
00:47:19,645 --> 00:47:21,145
you'll stay with me, right?

559
00:47:23,285 --> 00:47:25,385
Because I'm never letting you go again.

560
00:47:50,945 --> 00:47:52,665
Why didn't you come out for the last visit?

561
00:47:53,445 --> 00:47:55,515
Just because. I didn't want to see you.

562
00:47:57,215 --> 00:47:58,915
But I sent you so many letters.

563
00:48:00,355 --> 00:48:01,795
I couldn't be bothered to read them.

564
00:48:07,765 --> 00:48:08,765
What?

565
00:48:09,795 --> 00:48:11,165
This is just who I am.

566
00:48:11,895 --> 00:48:13,835
Selfish and rotten to the core.

567
00:48:16,705 --> 00:48:18,625
Did you think if you just
said a few nice words,

568
00:48:19,035 --> 00:48:21,745
I'd burst into tears and cry, "Mommy"?

569
00:48:23,415 --> 00:48:25,575
Are you frustrated it's not
going the way you planned?

570
00:48:29,315 --> 00:48:30,485
That's not it.

571
00:48:31,685 --> 00:48:33,955
I'm just glad you're healthy and safe.

572
00:48:34,485 --> 00:48:35,955
That's what I came to see.

573
00:48:47,535 --> 00:48:49,165
We're mother and daughter,

574
00:48:50,175 --> 00:48:54,145
but we have nothing to talk about, do we?

575
00:48:57,975 --> 00:48:59,345
Looks like our time is about up.

576
00:48:59,945 --> 00:49:01,045
I'm going now.

577
00:49:02,815 --> 00:49:03,855
Min Seo.

578
00:49:08,825 --> 00:49:09,895
It's okay.

579
00:49:10,525 --> 00:49:12,655
You can be even more selfish, even meaner.

580
00:49:14,365 --> 00:49:16,435
And if you're still upset after all that,

581
00:49:17,635 --> 00:49:18,935
that's okay too.

582
00:49:20,065 --> 00:49:21,135
I'll just

583
00:49:21,935 --> 00:49:23,205
be here again next week,

584
00:49:24,205 --> 00:49:25,735
waiting for you.

585
00:49:50,465 --> 00:49:54,735
I once couldn't bring myself to
tell someone to keep on living.

586
00:49:55,835 --> 00:49:57,995
When faced with the pain
they had to endure every day,

587
00:49:58,135 --> 00:50:00,745
how irresponsible those
words would have sounded.

588
00:50:17,895 --> 00:50:19,455
(The late Jo Yoo Jeong)

589
00:50:23,535 --> 00:50:24,671
("Lee Jun Hyeok Murder Case")

590
00:50:24,695 --> 00:50:25,771
("The Late Jo is No
Longer a Murder Suspect")

591
00:50:25,795 --> 00:50:27,635
("Police Confirmed Her
as an Innocent Victim")

592
00:50:30,105 --> 00:50:32,105
(The late Jo Yoo Jeong)

593
00:50:35,505 --> 00:50:38,645
Sometimes, I would lie,
hoping the lie would come true.

594
00:50:39,845 --> 00:50:42,285
Don't you dare die. You kill them instead.

595
00:50:42,345 --> 00:50:44,945
You have to live with that fire,
tenaciously, just to spite them.

596
00:50:54,195 --> 00:50:55,195
However,

597
00:50:55,825 --> 00:50:57,065
now that it has come to this...

598
00:50:57,265 --> 00:50:59,135
You'll never be free from that night.

599
00:51:02,405 --> 00:51:05,135
Because I can crush you
like this whenever I want.

600
00:51:08,405 --> 00:51:10,615
The reason I couldn't speak

601
00:51:11,875 --> 00:51:13,885
about what happened...

602
00:51:14,645 --> 00:51:15,845
After all,

603
00:51:16,345 --> 00:51:17,715
you're not going to say a word.

604
00:51:18,385 --> 00:51:19,745
You never could back then, either.

605
00:51:20,455 --> 00:51:23,525
- Because I was scared.
- Because I was sexually assaulted.

606
00:51:28,265 --> 00:51:29,565
You did well.

607
00:51:33,835 --> 00:51:36,535
In the end, I survived.

608
00:51:37,135 --> 00:51:38,305
And now,

609
00:51:38,805 --> 00:51:40,975
for those of you listening to my voice,

610
00:51:41,545 --> 00:51:42,675
I truly hope

611
00:51:43,345 --> 00:51:45,275
that you will keep on living.

612
00:51:50,685 --> 00:51:53,525
It's not because the pain
will suddenly stop one day,

613
00:51:53,925 --> 00:51:57,355
or because of some miracle
that will wash your scars away.

614
00:52:11,475 --> 00:52:14,605
We can never get back
the things we've lost,

615
00:52:15,475 --> 00:52:16,975
(CEO Kang Shin Jae)

616
00:52:17,075 --> 00:52:18,745
And sometimes we must bear

617
00:52:19,315 --> 00:52:21,215
the weight of our lives all by ourselves.

618
00:52:24,885 --> 00:52:26,185
But despite all that,

619
00:52:26,755 --> 00:52:28,625
as long as you are alive,

620
00:52:29,155 --> 00:52:32,925
please remember that
you will always be the victor.

621
00:52:39,435 --> 00:52:41,905
Look. What happened to you

622
00:52:42,065 --> 00:52:44,775
ended up happening to
your daughter all over again.

623
00:52:47,405 --> 00:52:48,905
As long as you are still breathing,

624
00:52:49,275 --> 00:52:53,685
the malice of those wanting you
harmed will have failed forever.

625
00:53:01,985 --> 00:53:04,895
What took you so long? I
was freezing to death out here.

626
00:53:06,255 --> 00:53:08,041
- It's freezing. Let's go.
- Have you been waiting long?

627
00:53:08,065 --> 00:53:11,395
And so, for us who live on with our scars,

628
00:53:12,735 --> 00:53:14,835
every moment of every day is brilliant,

629
00:53:16,005 --> 00:53:17,105
and honourable.

630
00:53:38,255 --> 00:53:39,795
(One way)

631
00:53:39,855 --> 00:53:42,465
(Law Firm Listen and Join)

632
00:53:43,665 --> 00:53:46,065
So he got probation again?

633
00:53:46,335 --> 00:53:49,511
I guess our judge thought
the assailant's apology letter

634
00:53:49,535 --> 00:53:51,005
was a work of literary genius.

635
00:53:51,305 --> 00:53:55,445
Diminished capacity, first
offence, a family to support.

636
00:53:56,605 --> 00:53:58,575
It's always the same old song and dance.

637
00:54:00,085 --> 00:54:01,085
Seriously,

638
00:54:01,585 --> 00:54:03,955
how can a father with a
daughter do something like that?

639
00:54:06,755 --> 00:54:07,825
Gosh.

640
00:54:09,955 --> 00:54:12,355
How's your mom?

641
00:54:13,595 --> 00:54:17,765
Yes, you know my mom.
I visited her last week,

642
00:54:18,195 --> 00:54:19,635
and she's got more energy than I do.

643
00:54:22,335 --> 00:54:25,105
I got resignation letters
from three associates today.

644
00:54:26,175 --> 00:54:29,305
There's no room left in my
drawer. It's overflowing with them.

645
00:54:34,915 --> 00:54:36,615
Sounds like tteokbokki is here.

646
00:54:36,755 --> 00:54:39,185
Already? We ordered
less than ten minutes ago.

647
00:54:39,455 --> 00:54:40,555
I'll get it.

648
00:54:58,175 --> 00:54:59,235
Please help me.

649
00:55:17,595 --> 00:55:20,595
Why don't you have
something warm to drink first?

650
00:55:37,815 --> 00:55:39,275
Well, I

651
00:55:39,845 --> 00:55:41,985
saw on social media...

652
00:55:59,235 --> 00:56:03,205
(Honour)

653
00:56:55,125 --> 00:56:59,325
(Honour)
